<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11356&amp;p=130117#p130117"><![CDATA[
Or just compare to all colors in the palette using a metric like ((r1-r2)^2*3 + (g1-g2)^2*6 + (b1-b2)^2). You're going to have to do this comparing for each pixel even if the user provides an 8- or 32-digit list of palette indices.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sat Jun 21, 2014 8:36 pm</p><hr />
